  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Audit Partner",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p>We are seeking accomplished and visionary professionals to join our assurance practice as Audit Partners, serving clients internationally across diverse industries and driving strategic growth.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Job Highlights</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Leadership role with strategic impact</p>\n<p>· Friendly and collaborative culture</p>\n<p>· Attractive remuneration package with partnership potential</p>\n<p>· Modern open-concept office near MRT stations</p>\n<p>· Opportunities for continuous professional development</p>\n<p>· Work-life balance with 5-day work week</p>\n<p>· Prospects for overseas engagements post-travel restrictions</p>\n<p>· Inclusive, understanding management and dynamic environment</p>\n<p>· High level of autonomy and decision-making influence</p>\n<p>· Strong support team to manage audit operations</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Provide leadership and strategic direction for the audit practice</p>\n<p>· Manage a portfolio of key clients and deliver exceptional audit services</p>\n<p>· Oversee PCAOB and IPO audit engagements and ensure regulatory compliance</p>\n<p>· Maintain and develop strong client relationships while building new business opportunities</p>\n<p>· Oversee quality assurance and ensure full compliance with professional and regulatory standards</p>\n<p>· Guide and mentor audit teams to develop technical excellence (e.g., SFRS, IFRS, US GAAP, ACRA, PCAOB)</p>\n<p>· Participate actively in firm-wide leadership, operational planning, and growth initiatives</p>\n<p>· Lead technical discussions on complex accounting and auditing matters</p>\n<p>· Drive innovation and continuous improvement in audit methodology and practice management</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Degree in Accountancy or equivalent professional qualification (e.g., CPA, ACCA)</p>\n<p>· At least 10 years of progressive experience in external audit</p>\n<p>· Proven track record in client management and business development</p>\n<p>· Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</p>\n<p>· Demonstrated leadership, integrity, and sound judgment</p>\n<p>· Ability to inspire, mentor, and lead audit teams effectively</p>\n<p>· Entrepreneurial mindset with strategic and commercial acumen</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified. Thank you for applying.</p>",
